caption.p: Time course analysis of alkaloid levels in different treatment groups. ( A) Allocryptopine. ( B) Protopine. ( C) Dihydrochelerythrine. ( D) Dihydrosanguinarine. ( E) Chelerythrine. ( F) Sanguinarine. Asterisks denote significant changes (Tukey’s test, * indicates P < 0.05, ** indicates P < 0.01, *** indicates P < 0.005, and **** indicates P < 0.001) compared with the 0 h group.
